        <h1>
          Why pack light?
        </h1>
        <p>
          When wild camping and completing multi-day hikes, every extra kilo counts. There is a whole plethora equipment the typical hiker will have with them – tent, clothes, food, cooking equipment, sleeping equipment and more. This can quickly take its toll if carrying bulky and heavy equipment. 
        </p>
      </section>
      <article>
        <h2>Light packing principles</h2>
        <p>
          The principles of packing light, with the extreme end known ‘ultralight’, was pioneered in the US by hikers completing long distance hikes such as the ~4300km Pacific Coast Trail. Irish hikers may not have quite the same distances to worry about, but the principles can greatly improve the enjoyment of enjoying the many trails our island has to offer! The video below from Salomon provides a good overview of the principles.
        </p>
        <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZPHMw9rSW18" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        <p>
          <b>Packing light has a number of immediate benefits:</b>
        </p>
        <ul class="list-no-style">
          <li>Go farther than you could before without getting fatigued.</l>
            <li>If you’re short on time, get to your destination faster</li>
            <li>Reduce your chance of injury</li>
            <li>More comfort and freedom as you won’t be so weighed down!</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
