  <article>
    <h2>Why pack light in Ireland?</h2>
    <p>
      Ireland has a number of advantages that facilitate packing light compared to countries with different terrains and climates:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>No need for mosquito nets, bear canisters, or other bulky equipment to deter animals or critters</li>
      <li>Relatively mild climate, so packing for extreme cold temperatures is rarely needed</li>
      <li>The most remote part of the country (Nephin Beg Mountains, Mayo) is still only 6km from the nearest road – meaning the chances of being stranded or in danger due to missing equipment is relatively low.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
